com.parse4cn1.command

Class ParseCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.parse4cn1.command.ParseCommand
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParseDeleteCommand, ParseDownloadCommand, ParseGetCommand, ParsePostCommand, ParsePutCommand, ParseUploadCommand

    public abstract class ParseCommand
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates a network request to be made to the Parse REST API using any of the supported HTTP verbs.

      • setupDefaultHeaders

        protected void setupDefaultHeaders()
                            throws ParseException
        Adds the default headers (e.g., ParseConstants.HEADER_APPLICATION_ID and ParseConstants.HEADER_CLIENT_KEY) associated with Parse REST API calls and (@Link ParseConstants#HEADER_SESSION_TOKEN) if there is a current user. The content type is also set to ParseConstants.CONTENT_TYPE_JSON by default and can be overruled in setUpRequest(com.codename1.io.ConnectionRequest).
        Throws:
        ParseException - if anything goes wrong.
